<!--
  Template: Abandoned Cart with Benefits Breakdown
  File: 02-cart-recovery-benefits.mjml
  Category: abandoned-cart / cart-recovery
  
  Purpose:
  Re-engage customers who left items in cart by showcasing product benefits and addressing objections.
  Uses educational approach with detailed features grid + FAQ section to overcome hesitation.
  
  When to send:
  - 2-4 hours after cart abandonment (first reminder)
  - 24 hours after abandonment (second reminder in series)
  - For high-value items (>$30) where education drives conversion
  
  Personalize:
  - {{first_name}}
  - {{product_name}} (e.g., "NYA body cream")
  - {{product_image}} - hero 16:9 product shot
  - {{cart_url}} for "Complete my order" CTA
  - Brand colors (#208e7c primary, #fff6ed background)
  
  Tested on:
  Gmail (web/mobile), Outlook, Apple Mail, iOS Mail
  
  Notes:
  - Marketing email (unsubscribe required - included in footer)
  - Educational approach vs. discount-driven (keeps brand value high)
  - 6-point benefits grid reduces perceived risk
  - FAQ section preemptively handles objections (texture, sensitivity, results)
  - No urgency/scarcity tactics = softer, trustworthy tone
  - Works best for premium/luxury products where trust > price
  - 16:9 hero image optimized for mobile preview
  - "Reply to this email" = builds personal connection
  
  A/B test suggestions:
  - Subject line: Benefits-focused vs. "You forgot something"
  - CTA copy: "Complete my order" vs. "Get my cream now"
  - Add social proof section (reviews/testimonials)
  
  Conversion goal:
  Primary: Recover 8-15% of abandoned carts
  Secondary: Educate on product value (nurture for future purchase)
  Tertiary: Reduce support queries via FAQ section
-->
